# vlans 
- default vlan: vlan 1
- can't be deleted, can only be disabled
- native vlan: 

# trunking
- also known as tagging
- mmultiple vlans on a single port
- connects multiple vlans together

# arp
- switch forwards arp request out of every port it has an active connection on
- it asks if the machine is using a particular IP addr
- clients that receive it will send arp reply if they have that IP

# DAI

# DAI implementation
- helps prevent mitm attacks
- can only be assigned to VLANS, not ports
- ports need to be grouped into VLANs
- designates ports as trusted and untrusted
- trusted ports: ports connected to internal server 
- untrusted: ports connected to user devices